description.p:
Nonane triisocyanate (NTI or 4-isocyanatomethyl-1,8-octane
diisocyanate) is a known material. Various uses for NTI have been
suggested. See, e.g., U.S. Patents 4,314,048; 5,714,564; 5,854,301;
6,084,051; 6,090,939; 6,100,326; 6,291,578; 6,399,691; 6,432,485;
6,433,072; 6,531,535; 6,566,444; and 6,605,669.

The diols and polyols useful herein have number average molecular
weights of from about 62 to about 600 and preferably from about 62 to
about 200. Specifically useful diol and polyols include ethylene glycol;
diethylene glycol; triethylene glycol; propylene glycol; dipropylene glycol;
butane diols; hexane diols; glycerin; trimethylolethane; trimethylolpropane;
pentaerythritol; hexane triols; mannitol; sorbitol; glucose; fructose;
mannose; sucrose; and propoxylated and/or ethoxylated adducts of any of
the above-noted hydroxy functional materials having number average
molecular weights of up to about 600.
